 ### Stateless Functional Component

```js
// Function must be Capitalized
const MyComponent = function () {
  // Return JSX
  const JSX = <div>My First Component</div>;
  return JSX;
};
```
> Stateless:
> 
> One that can receive data and render it, but does not manage or track changes to that data

### Render Component with ES6 Syntax

```js
// Declare Class
class MyComponent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props);
  }
// Call Render and Return Div
  render() {
  return (
      <div><h1>Hello React!</h1></div>
    );
  }
};
```

### Render Child Component

```js
// Declare Child Component
const ChildComponent = () => {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>I am the child</p>
    </div>
  );
};

// Render  Component

class ParentComponent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props);
  }
  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <h1>I am the parent</h1>
        <ChildComponent> </ChildComponent>
      </div>
    );
  }
}

```
